            "h2_text": false,
            "content": "<p><strong>SLAM and ARCA SGR <\/strong>The partnership between SLAM and Furio Benussi actually started on occasion of Barcolana #48 in 2016, in which the Trieste-born sailor raced to victory aboard the <em>Alfa Romeo <\/em>boat, after which he went on to win the next two editions, with the Maxi Yacht <em>Spirit of Portopiccolo<\/em> (former Morning Glory).<\/p><p>The relationship is based on a shared <strong>passion for the sea and for competition and on the desire for excellence<\/strong>.  The packed schedule of events of the 100’ ARCA SGR, with a team combining highly experienced professionals with promising youngsters in the Olympic classes, offers SLAM a unique opportunity for dialogue, <strong>research <\/strong>and <strong>innovation <\/strong>on its technical clothing, which is used in the various regattas in all kinds of sea and wind conditions, a genuine floating workshop on which to test the latest oilskins:<a href=\"https:\/\/www.slam.com\/it\/products\/man-pro-racing-jacket-a170002s00?_pos=3&_fid=93320581d&_ss=c\"><strong>PRO SAILING JACKET<\/strong><\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.slam.com\/it\/products\/man-pro-racing-long-john-a171003s00\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PRO SAILING LONG JOHN<\/strong><\/a><\/p>",
