        "green_label": "",
        "white_label": "",
        "title": "",
        "content": "<p>SLAM and the Fast and Furio Sailing Team promote sailing as a sport among young people, with dedicated projects, and also work alongside the One Ocean Foundation in its activities to protect the sea.<\/p><p><br\/><\/p><p>Furio Benussi is, in fact, an Ocean Defender of the foundation, thanks to the project for <strong>recovery of a hull (Wild Thing)<\/strong> that had fallen into disuse and been left completely abandoned in a yard on the island of Minorca, for which, at the Genoa Boat Show on Friday 23 September, he received the <em>Environmental Product Declaration certificate<\/em>, on a yacht recycling project.<\/p><p><br\/><\/p><p>The Fast and Furio Sailing Team and Arca Fondi SGR also support the Fondazione Laureus Italia, Il Porto dei Piccoli and the Fondazione Io Do Una Mano. Io Do Una Mano, an Italian non-profit foundation, organizes the 3D printing of artificial limbs with recycled plastic to help children who, as a result of accident or illness, need these prosthetics. Sailing for Children, created by “Il Porto dei Piccoli” together with the Gaslini Children's Hospital in Genoa, is an initiative in which several youngsters got the chance to embark with the crew of the Furio Sailing Team, who organized very special training sessions for these young sailors.<\/p>",
